LAGOS – The MotorMechs and Technicians Association of Nigeria (MOMTAN) has elected Alhail Maruf Adebayo Arowolo as its national president at a keenly contested election on Thursday in Iwo, Osun State.He will preside over the affairs of the association for the next four years. He took over from Prince J.0. Omotosho, who is the immediate past president of the association. In his acceptance speech, Arowolo, who is the erstwhile chairman of the Lagos State chapter of the association, described his election as a profound honour and responsibility and commended all those that supported him and contributed to the success of his election. He called on members of the association to partner with him to take the body to greater heights, adding that the victory belonged to Nigerian youths who are in the trying times are eager to acquire technical skills, especially in mechatronícs training. He promised to use his position as the national president of the association to empower youths throughout the thirty-six states of Nigeria to acquire technical skills. The national president of MOMTAN called on members to put all grievances and grudges aside to move forward in the bid to move the association forward. He stressed the need for improved productivity among members and urged them to acquire skills that will enable them to give high quality to their clients and put their vehicles in peak mechanical performance.